description:
**Feature Request**

Toaster should support both dark and light mode themes to improve usability in different environments. The following enhancements are requested:

- Add a comprehensive dark mode theme for all UI elements
- Ensure there is a clear and complete light mode theme for all UI elements
- Provide a user-accessible toggle to switch between light and dark modes
- Add an option for Toaster to follow the system appearance preference (auto-switch between light/dark)

---

**Relevant Code References:**

- Theme color variables and system preference detection are currently handled here:
  - [`frontend/src/app/globals.css`](https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/toaster/blob/d4cdcca2d902f3a7d07aecd9f9423aceb4cce8fe/frontend/src/app/globals.css#L1-L26)
    ```css
    :root {
      --background: #ffffff;
      --foreground: #171717;
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      :root {
        --background: #0a0a0a;
        --foreground: #ededed;
      }
    }
    ```
  - Usage of theme variables in page UI:
    - [`frontend/src/app/page.tsx`](https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/toaster/blob/d4cdcca2d902f3a7d07aecd9f9423aceb4cce8fe/frontend/src/app/page.tsx)

The toggle UI and logic need to be added. Current theme switching is automatic via CSS media query, and both modes are already partially defined in the code above. Please complete both light and dark theme definitions and provide a manual toggle and system preference option.

---

This would allow users to customize their experience and better integrate Toaster with their desktop or browser appearance settings.
